The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | CAB secy no more
                                                                                                                       7                                      CAB secy no more
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Arun Mitra, the Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) joint secretary, passed away on Wednesday afternoon following a severe heart attack. He was 75. Mitra is survived by his wife and daughter. The CAB will remain closed on Thursday and Friday.         
	Mitra, who represented Belgachia United, served CAB for three decades in various capacities. He had been the assistant secretary from 1993-95. He was elected joint secretary in 2008 and earned unopposed a third term in the recently concluded AGM.         
	The CAB will now have to conduct a Special General Meeting within 60 days to elect a new joint secretary.                                                                                                                     
